      <div class="llms-section">
        <h2>What is Payxem?</h2>
        <p>Payxem is an online invoicing and payment tracking platform built for freelancers, consultants, and small businesses, especially in <strong>Pakistan, Bangladesh, and other underserved markets</strong> where PayPal is unavailable or restricted.</p>
        <p>It provides a <strong>PayPal alternative</strong> and Stripe solution for freelancers in Pakistan who need to invoice international clients, accept online payments, and get paid without expensive monthly subscriptions. Users can create invoices, send payment links, and track payments while actual payment processing is handled by third-party providers such as PayPal, Stripe, and cryptocurrency networks.</p>
        <p>Payxem does not operate as a bank or payment processor. It does not hold or custody funds. It acts as a coordination and tracking layer for financial activity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="llms-section">
        <h2>Core Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Professional invoice creation with line items, tax, and due dates</li>
          <li>Payment links and QR codes for quick payments</li>
          <li>Ledger-based wallet tracking with real-time balance</li>
          <li>Multi-currency support (52+ currencies with live exchange rates)</li>
          <li>Multiple payment methods (PayPal, credit/debit cards, cryptocurrency including USDT, BTC, ETH)</li>
          <li>XEM reward points program for every transaction</li>
          <li>Identity verification (KYC) for payout eligibility</li>
          <li>Biometric login, PIN lock, and encrypted authentication</li>
          <li>Mobile-first progressive web app (PWA)</li>
          <li>Free withdrawals via IBAN, crypto wallet, or Wise</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="llms-section">
        <h2>Who Uses Payxem?</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Freelancers in Pakistan, Bangladesh, and South Asia</strong> (designers, developers, writers, marketers, video editors)</li>
          <li>Remote workers and consultants who need to receive international payments</li>
          <li>Small businesses and service providers looking for a PayPal or Stripe alternative</li>
          <li>Digital professionals in underserved markets where global payment platforms are restricted</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="llms-section">
        <h2>Regional Focus</h2>
        <p>Payxem is designed as an <strong>online payment solution for Pakistan</strong> and similar regions where PayPal is banned, restricted, or unavailable. Freelancers in Pakistan can use Payxem to invoice international clients, accept credit card and crypto payments, and withdraw to local bank accounts via IBAN or Wise.</p>
        <p>It also serves freelancers in <strong>Bangladesh, India, UAE, Sri Lanka, and Nepal</strong> where access to Stripe and PayPal is limited.</p>
        <p><strong>Countries served:</strong> Pakistan, Bangladesh, India, United Arab Emirates, Sri Lanka, Nepal, and 50+ countries worldwide.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="llms-section">
        <h2>Pricing</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>No monthly fees</strong> or setup costs</li>
          <li>Transaction fee: <strong>3.5% + $0.30</strong> per payment received</li>
          <li>Clients can choose to cover the processing fee at checkout</li>
          <li>Free withdrawals (standard processing time)</li>
          <li>XEM reward points reduce effective costs over time</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="llms-section">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Create a free account at <a href="https://app.payxem.com">app.payxem.com</a></li>
          <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Create a professional invoice or payment link</li>
          <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Share with your client. They choose how to pay (card, PayPal, crypto)</li>
          <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Track earnings and withdraw when ready</li>
        </ul>
